column2: Test Case 1:Verify that Simple Fixed Auction response is not allowed for Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 2:Verify that only one auction response per side (i.e. buysell) is allowed per user for a Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 3:Verify that initiator cannot execute when T1 timer is active for a Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 4:Verify that auction ends normally when there are no responses for a Percentage Simple product and T2 timer ends
Test Case 5:Verify that auction ends prematurely when there are no responses for a Percentage Simple product and Initiator withdraws from auction during T2 timer
Test Case 6:Verify that crossing responses for a Percentage Simple product will trade if Initiator withdraws from auction during T2 timer
Test Case 7:Verify that crossing responses trade with each other for a Percentage Simple product and FLEX auction is timed out
Test Case 8:Verify Order trade when there are crossing Responses and Initiator trades fully with BUY side Percentage Simple order
Test Case 10:Verify Order trade when there are crossing Responses and Initiator trades partially with SELL side Percentage Simple order
Test Case 11:Verify that auction reponses will be cancelled when there are non-crossing responses and Initiator withdraws from Percentage Simple FLEX Auction
Test Case 12:Verify allocation of responses when there are crossing customer and non-customer responses for Percentage Simple FLEX auction and initiator executes
Test Case 13:Verify Initiator trades with Percentage Simple FLEX responses (Buy side) at multiple price points
Test Case 14:Verify Initiator trades with Percentage Simple FLEX responses (Sell side) at multiple price points
Test Case 15:Verify that Simple non customer orders will be allocated based on Price time priority for Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 16:Verify that Customer will not get priority over other orders if the Allocation startegy is set as Customer priority for Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 17:Verify that crossing responses trade with each other if it is better priced than Initiator s order
Test Case 18:Verify that remaining quantity of Initiator s IOC contingent order will be cancelled after partial fill for Percentage Simple FLEX auction
Test Case 19:Verify that user can cancel its response for FLEX auction for a Percentage Simple product
Test Case 20:Verify Trade allocation when Initiator Order is present and Cross Market Exist
Test Case 21:Verify trade between Auction responses when there is not Initiator Order present
Test Case 22:Verify FLEX trade are only Auction responses on the opposite side of Initiator Order. IO is on Sell Side
Test Case 23:Verify FLEX trade are only Auction responses on the opposite side of Initiator Order. IO is on Buy Side
